Italian Endrio Leoni won a photo-finish  sprint to take the fifth stage of the Tour of Italy here on Thursday.
It was his second success of the Giro, after he won a mass sprint on  Sunday at Bologna.
Russian Evgeni Berzin retained the overall race lead after the 158km run  between Campobasso and Melfi.
Another Italian, Fabio Baldato, came second while Spanish race favourite  Miguel Indurain came fifth.
